# net-admin
A C++ tool to monitor TCP connections (IPv4 & IPv6) on Linux.

## Installation on Fedora
Install dependencies:

sudo dnf install gcc-c++ fmt-devel nlohmann-json-devel


Compile: 
g++ -std=c++17 -o net-admin net_admin.cpp -lfmt

Chmod if needed:
chmod +x net-admin


Usage:
net-admin [--interval <seconds>] [--filter-state <state>] [--filter-ip <ip>] [--filter-port <port>] [--output-format <text|json>]

Example:
sudo net-admin --interval 5 --filter-state ESTABLISHED --filter-ip 127.0.0.1
